When you try to configure the hg executable, it can fail with:
{noformat}
Bad hg executable: No version string found in output of /usr/bin/hg version
{noformat}

FishEye uses _"hg version"_ to retrieve the Mercurial/Hg version.
Hg can report version in OS's locale.

E.g. English:
{noformat}
Mercurial Distributed SCM (version 1.8.4+20110601)
{noformat}
Italian:
{noformat}
Mercurial SCM Distribuito (versione 1.8.4+20110601)
{noformat}

FishEye uses pattern matching to extract version:
{noformat}
HG_VERSION_PATTERN_STRING = "version\\s([\\d\\.\\+]+)"
{noformat}
This fails with some non-English locales.

*Workaround*
* Changing system's location should work (observed in Windows).

The SAL API documentation states that {{UserProfile.getProfilePictureUri()}}
bq. The URI will either be relative to the application's base URI, or absolute if the profile picture is being served by an external server

Currently, when the avatar URI is using the internal avatar service, the implementation returns a URI that includes the context path (which is also included in the base URI).  This is incorrect according to the documentation and also makes it difficult for plugins to construct an absolute URI for the avatar picture.

The SAL API documentation states that {{UserProfile.getProfilePageUri()}}
bq. Returns a URI for the user's profile page. The URI will be relative to the application's base URI

Currently, the implementation always returns a URI for {{/profile/viewAuthorMapping.do}}, which does not point to the user's profile page.

