Because we do a git clone --bare when cloning the git repository for slurping in FishEye, any .mailmap set in the source repo is not available in the clone.

This means, the link displayed in the following log message is incorrect:

{code}
[java] 2011-07-15 16:56:39,615 WARN  - You may be able to adjust committer names if you have used multiple email addresses per committer. Please see http://confluence.atlassian.com/x/MgJRDg
{code}

Specifically:
{quote}
Rewriting history is also valid for git (detailed below), but git has an easier alternative, using the .mailmap file. This allows the git repository to report to FishEye different name and email addresses than were actually used by the author — this will not affect any other repositories, unless they also get the .mailmap file in their local repositories. See the git shortlog man page for more details. Once you set this up, you will need to go to the administration console in FishEye for your repository and under the 'Maintenance' tab, select 'Re-clone and Re-index'.
{quote}

The Display URL option in the application link is not configurable

*Steps to replicate the problem:*
# In current configure application link click on the configure link via _administration >> Application Links >> Configure >> Application Detail_
# Edit the display URL and try to update 

The configuration does not change and upon the clicking on the update the UI just hang

*Workaround*
# Shut down Fisheye server
# Edit the config.xml find the following example tag:
{code}
<property name="applinks.admin.0f89de4c-ca53-3a8b-a17b-0286507f8741.display.url" value="<some URL>"/>
{code}

Please change the <some URL> value to URL link which encoded for example:
{code}
http%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A8340%2Fjira431
{code}

Decode value of the above URL is:
{code}
http://localhost:8340/jira431
{code}

See the [following|http://mercurial.selenic.com/wiki/ApiChanges] in 2. Changes after 1.8:

bq. Various functions have been moved from cmdutil.py to scmutil.py, including revrange/revsingle/revpair and match/matchall/matchfiles

Also - at the top of the page, it seems we don't have a process for detecting breaking changes in mercurial:

h1. How to keep your extension compatible

* Subscribe to this page to keep up-to-date on changes
* Mark your calendar to test your extension before our scheduled releases (Mar 1, Jul 1, Nov 1)
* Use introspection in helper functions to choose which interface to call, for example:

{code}
def updatedir(*args, **kwargs):
    if hasattr(patch, 'updatedir'):
        patch.updatedir(*args, **kwargs)
    else:
        cmdutil.updatedir(*args, **kwargs)
{code}
* Use inspect.getargspec() to deal with changing argument lists

Document how the User Management can be transitioned from Built-In to Crowd.

Something like the following options:
{quote}
1. Change the User Account so that it can have the *Auth Type* field set to "crowd" instead of "built-in" (click *edit* for the user entry). This will keep the user with the Display Name that is stored in the FeCru DB, not the one stored in Crowd.

2. If the user already exist as a build-in entry, when syncing with Crowd, the user will not be fetched into the FeCru DB because it already exists there. If the user name is exactly the same, you can delete the built-in user and then sync with Crowd again. The exact same user name will allow all the reviews from the old user to be assigned to the new user. This will also bring in the Crowd Display Name for the user.
{quote}
